subject: p11413236
History: Chest pain and wheezing in the setting of mast cell degranulation crisis.
Findings: A Port-A-Cath terminating in the upper part of the superior vena cava appears unchanged since the more recent of the prior two studies. The patient is status post sternotomy. A calcified prevascular lymph node appears unchanged. The cardiac, mediastinal and hilar contours appear stable. The lung volumes are low. Streaky basilar opacity consistent with minor scarring is similar in the lingula. There is no substantial parenchymal opacity.
